  "orchestration_decision": "delegate",
  "decision_notes": "The problem requires deriving the equation of state for a polymer chain under adiabatic conditions. This involves calculating the partition function for a freely jointed chain, determining the internal energy and entropy as functions of extension, and applying the first law of thermodynamics for an adiabatic process.",
  "helpers": [
    {
      "label": "statistical_mechanics_expert",
      "instructions": "Calculate the partition function Z(x, T) for a freely jointed chain of n segments of length l extended to a total end-to-end distance x. Provide the expression for the entropy S(x, T) as a function of x, n, l, and T."
    },
    {
      "label": "thermodynamics_expert",
      "instructions": "Given the entropy S(x, T) and the internal energy U(T) of a freely jointed chain, derive the adiabatic constraint S(x, T) = constant. Use this to find the relationship between temperature T and extension x during an adiabatic process. Then, use the relation F = -dU/dx (at constant S) or F = T(dS/dx) to find the force F(x)."
    }
  ],
  "synthesis_brief": "Combine the entropy expression from the statistical mechanics expert with the thermodynamic derivation to find the specific functional form of F(x). Ensure the final result accounts for the adiabatic change in temperature as the chain is stretched."
}

